butterfly2.4/fat_finger_move.description: A fat (noisy) finger moving from left to right.

butterfly2.4/move_jumped_at_end.description:
Feedback showed the cursor jumping after lifting the finger.
    Make sure it does not happen.

link/2_finger_delayed_click.description:
This test was artificially created. Both fingers touch down at exactly the
    same time, which is not usually happening for thumb and finger.
    So we treat them as both fingers and right click.

link/base_right_click_1_sec_interval.description:
The beginning of this log shows small one-finger movements,
    so movement at the beginning is considered ok, while movement everywhere
    else should not happen.

link/button_click_merge_issue.description:
Issues with finger merging appear when multiple fingers touch down at
    the same time. These issues are usually resolved after 2, 3 hardware
    states. This test case shows the problem with a 3 finger click.

link/button_middle_click_variations.description:
Test if different variations of performing a middle click using
    the phyiscal button is working.

link/button_right_click_no_wiggle.description:
Same log as button_right_click_variations, but this time check
    for cursor wiggle between the down/up events!

link/button_right_click_variations.description:
Test if different variations of performing a right click using
    the phyiscal button is working.

link/fling_stop_order.description:
This test checks if fling stop events are sent before button events, as this
    is required by Chrome.

link/middle_button_with_thumb.description:
Classified thumbs used to induce problems with button detections,
    check if the middle click works.

link/pinch_false_positive_1.description:
The feedback report showed a pinch gesture where only motion should
    have happened. This test is passes as long as there is no
    pinch gesture happening.

link/pinch_false_positive_2.description:
The feedback report showed a pinch gesture where only motion should
    have happened. This test is passes as long as there is no
    pinch gesture happening.

link/pinch_variations.description: Pinch is currently not supported and work in progress.

link/resting_thumb_scroll.description:
Test if even with a resting (and moving) thumb we still get
    good scrolling and fling behavior

link/scroll_false_negatives.description:
A scrolling gesture with a resting thumb. Tricky part here is
    that the thumb has only a slightly higher pressure than
    the other contacts. Make sure scrolling works anyway.

link/ttc_with_palm.description:
The log contains some history of the palm with movement/scrolls.
    At the end there are two taps performed and we want to make sure
    they happen.

lumpy/right_when_left_click_intended.description:
Very nasty case with 2 palms appearing with one thumb all in the time
    frame of 300ms. The user intended to do a left click.

lumpy/scroll_without_fling.description:
Make sure there is no *real* fling.  Every time a scroll ends there
    should be a fling event, but in this case it's velocity must be 0

lumpy/scroll_without_fling2.description:
Make sure there is no *real* fling.  Every time a scroll ends there
    should be a fling event, but in this case it's velocity must be 0

parrot1.2/thumb_split_click.description:
Pointing finger followed by a thumb press for left click.
    Very nasty merge/split happening here.
